The new method of accounting for the receivable recognizes an offsetting receivable from the FDIC at the time problem loan expenses are incurred, based on the documented expectation that a qualifying loss event and reimbursement will occur in the future. The new method of accounting is analogous to indemnification asset accounting, and is more consistent in matching revenue with expense.
